@startuml
actor Admin

participant AdminApplication
control Controller
entity ImageService
entity ItemService
database Firestore

== Form Submission ==

Admin --> AdminApplication : Fill out item form (includes image URL)
AdminApplication --> Controller : Submit form data

== Validation ==

Controller --> Controller : Validate form fields
Controller --> Controller : Determine item type (painting, photo...)

== Image Creation ==

Controller --> ImageService : Create image entry
ImageService --> Firestore : Save image
Firestore --> ImageService : Return image ID

== Item Creation ==

Controller --> ItemService : Create item with image ID
ItemService --> Firestore : Save item in specific collection
Firestore --> ItemService : Confirm item creation

== Final Feedback ==

ItemService --> Controller : Item created successfully
Controller --> AdminApplication : Success message shown

@enduml
